skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "8de4ae2c-9f34-440b-b13e-5c1d8a3cd3f7", "value": "Protect and maintain the historic character of the landscape resource."}
{"id": "55d2247b-2777-4b15-9906-3342b9e7f251", "value": "Replace damaged or dead natural original/historic plant material when necessary."}

{"id": "44593024-6f8d-45db-b572-d0a9ca1c0f77", "value": "Use the same species or, if not available, a similar species that resembles the size and form of the removed vegetation. Substitute cultivars of original plants when originals cannot be located."}

{"id": "740e4cb9-88c0-4bf8-b586-3c9c8db904d1", "value": "When rehabilitating or modifying landscape resources, respect the historic relationship between the built and natural resources to ensure the preservation of the landscape design."}

{"id": "6a35d4e1-fb93-4808-b6c9-148a2fa54dcb", "value": "When replacing non-original/non-historic plant material, use plant species known to be on site during the appropriate sub-period defined for the Home. Substitute cultivars of period-appropriate plant species when originals cannot be located."}
